.Dd April 14, 2026
.Dt NOD-SEND 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm nod-send
.Nd notify-send-compatible CLI for nod
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl u Ar level
.Op Fl t Ar msec
.Op Fl a Ar app
.Op Fl i Ar icon
.Op Fl c Ar cat
.Op Fl h Ar type:name:value
.Op Fl p
.Op Fl r Ar id
.Op Fl e
.Op Fl w
.Op Fl A Oo Ar name Ns = Oc Ns Ar label
.Ar summary
.Op Ar body
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a
.Xr notify-send 1
drop-in replacement written as a POSIX shell script. It speaks D-Bus
via
.Xr gdbus 1
and can wait for the notification to be closed, printing the invoked
action key to standard output.
.Pp
All arguments are
.Xr notify-send 1 Ns -compatible.
Flags that
.Xr nod 1
does not support (icon, category, transient) are accepted and
silently ignored so that scripts written for
.Xr notify-send 1
continue to work.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl u , Fl \-urgency Ns = Ns Ar LEVEL
Urgency:
.Sy low ,
.Sy normal ,
or
.Sy critical
(or numeric 0, 1, 2). Default:
.Sy normal .
.It Fl t , Fl \-expire-time Ns = Ns Ar MSEC
Expire timeout in milliseconds.
.Sy -1
means use the daemon default;
.Sy 0
means persistent (must click to dismiss).
.It Fl a , Fl \-app-name Ns = Ns Ar NAME
Application name. Default:
.Sy nod-send .
.It Fl i , Fl \-icon Ns = Ns Ar ICON
Ignored.
.Xr nod 1
does not render icons.
.It Fl c , Fl \-category Ns = Ns Ar TYPE
Ignored.
.It Fl h , Fl \-hint Ns = Ns Ar TYPE:NAME:VALUE
Set an arbitrary hint.
.Ar TYPE
may be
.Sy byte , int , uint32 , boolean , double ,
or
.Sy string .
Only
.Sy urgency
is meaningfully consumed by
.Xr nod 1 .
.It Fl p , Fl \-print-id
Print the notification id to standard output after sending.
.It Fl r , Fl \-replace-id Ns = Ns Ar ID
Replace an existing notification with the given id.
.It Fl e , Fl \-transient
Ignored.
.It Fl w , Fl \-wait
Block until the notification is closed.
.It Fl A , Fl \-action Ns = Ns Oo Ar NAME Ns = Oc Ns Ar LABEL
Register an action. Without an explicit
.Ar NAME ,
the key is
.Sy default .
Implies
.Fl w :
.Nm
will block until the notification is dismissed, and if an action is
invoked its key is printed to standard output.
.It Fl \-version
Print version and exit.
.It Fl ? , Fl \-help
Print brief usage and exit.
.El
.Sh WAIT BEHAVIOUR
When
.Fl A
or
.Fl w
is used,
.Nm
blocks on a
.Xr gdbus 1
.Sy monitor
stream. The wait is bounded to prevent indefinite hangs:
.Bl -tag -width "finite timeout "
.It Sy finite timeout
.Ar MSEC
/ 1000 + 3 seconds of slack.
.It Sy persistent No ( Fl t Sy 0 )
Unbounded. Kill with SIGINT to give up.
.It Sy default No ( Fl t Sy -1 No or unspecified)
33 seconds (assumes daemon default of ~10s plus slack).
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It 0
The notification was sent successfully.
.It 1
Argument parsing error or the
.Sy Notify
D-Bus call failed.
.El
.Sh OUTPUT
With
.Fl p ,
the notification id is printed on its own line right after dispatch.
.Pp
When waiting for an action, the invoked action key (e.g.
.Sy default )
is printed to standard output after the notification is closed.
Nothing is printed if the notification is dismissed without an action
being invoked.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Basic:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
nod-send "Hello" "This is a test"
nod-send -u critical -t 3000 "Critical" "Server down"
.Ed
.Pp
Default action:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
key=$(nod-send -A "Open" "New mail" "3 unread")
[ "$key" = default ] && xdg-open https://mail.example.com
.Ed
.Pp
Replace an existing notification:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
id=$(nod-send -p "Downloading" "0%")
# ...
nod-send -r "$id" "Downloading" "42%"
.Ed
.Sh DEPENDENCIES
.Xr gdbus 1
from
.Sy glib2 ,
a running session bus, and
.Xr nod 1
or another notification daemon owning
.Pa org.freedesktop.Notifications .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr nod 1 ,
.Xr notify-send 1 ,
.Xr gdbus 1
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Matteo Merola
